column5: cant remember it,its been a while! Or if some can figure it out from the photo.
Walleye= lxlxl divide by 2500 Pike+Muskies= lxlxl divide 3500 Bass=  lxlxl divide by 1700  It's not spot on the $ but very very close especially with the Pike & Walleye.  Randy

Thanks terry! Accord to my calc on the bass calc.Thats my mpb best at that pond.Last bucket I caught was a hair over 5 lbs.This one is around 7 give or take a few ounces. I wonder if this fish is a record fish for that pond?Got to be close for sure.
If you use Randy's formula...it's about 5.4 lbs...still a very nice fish.
"Bass" Formulas from fishing clubs. L X L X L divided by 1600 or L X G X G divided by 800
